# Decision log

> Tally of decisions the user has made at known forks the
> orchestrator would otherwise have to ask about. Used to develop
> confidence: after N consecutive same-answer responses to a
> low-risk fork, `/preferences` offers to capture the answer as a
> permanent preference.
>
> **Discipline doc:** `.claude/preferences.md` "Decision log
> discipline" — read it before writing entries.
> **Owning skill:** `/preferences` (read + prune); skills with
> known forks append entries via `bin/preferences-check log <id>
> <answer>`.
> **Auto-managed.** Do not hand-edit. To clear a fork's tally
> use `/preferences clear-log <id>` (or
> `bin/preferences-check clear-log <id>` directly).

The format below is regenerated when a known-fork answer is
appended. Aggregate fields recompute from the History list on each
write.

